loderunc ["levelset"]: Lode Runner, classic video game - press "s" to start a new game, press "r" to resume the last game, press "Esc" at the start of a level to quit the game, press any other key to start the level, use cursor keys to move your runner, press "y"/"x" (qwertz keyboard layout) to dig a hole to the left/right of the runner, press "c" to commit suicide. You have unlimited lives. If you finish a level, a file (ending .LEV) is created/updated which contains the actual level number. You may provide a level set. If no argument is given, the original level set provided in /DATA/LODERUN is loaded.
